& [SourceSet] is the checked research surface
  + [source_001] is Evan Miller, On the interaction of strain and vorticity for solutions of the Navier-Stokes equation
    = url: https://arxiv.org/html/2407.02691v2
    = relevance: gives strain-vorticity interaction identities and perturbative regularity criteria, clarifying depletion by advection without closing global regularity
  + [source_002] is Evan Miller, Finite-time blowup for a Navier-Stokes model equation for the self-amplification of strain
    = url: https://msp.org/apde/2023/16-4/apde-v16-n4-p03-p.pdf
    = relevance: shows reduced strain self-amplification can blow up, making omitted pressure/coupling terms proof-relevant periphery
  + [source_003] is Regularity criteria involving the middle eigenvalue of the strain tensor
    = url: https://www.aimsciences.org/article/doi/10.3934/eect.2020078
    = relevance: improves and extends middle-eigenvalue criteria, but remains criterion-level control rather than derived global control
  + [source_004] is Johnson and Meneveau, On the role of vorticity stretching and strain self-amplification in the turbulence energy cascade
    = url: https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/journal-of-fluid-mechanics/article/on-the-role-of-vorticity-stretching-and-strain-selfamplification-in-the-turbulence-energy-cascade/1E302903363C67A09F9B9E817533F935
    = relevance: supports pressure/viscous alteration of reduced dynamics in turbulence, but not as deterministic proof inequality
  + [source_005] is Modeling the pressure Hessian and viscous Laplacian in turbulence
    = url: https://biferale.web.roma2.infn.it/a130.pdf
    = relevance: treats pressure Hessian closure as a turbulence-modeling problem, emphasizing nonlocality and modeling rather than proof closure

